Get ready to make a name for yourself with this 1966 Ford Mustang Hardtop Coupe!  This two-door pony car is brimming with the athletic and handsome styling that has become an icon of the Mustang nameplate.  With white and vintage teal paint complimented by an very clean vintage teal interior this handsome devil is sure to turn heads.  Powered by a rebuilt 289 V-8 engine that is paired with 4-speed automatic transmission, this pretty pony is eager to get out on the road for a fast, fun, and fierce driving experience.  With only 86,000 miles you can rest assured that this Mustang will inspire passionate motoring for many years to come!

With production spanning through six generations, the Mustang created the "pony car" class of American automobiles.  These affordable sporty coupes were characterized by their long hoods and short rear decks.  Although some pony cars have seen a revival, the Mustang is the only original model to remain in uninterrupted production over five decades of development and revision. This Mustang offers the best of both worlds - classic style with modern appeal. This 1966 model is a first generation Mustang that has been stripped down and fully restored. It comes fully loaded with amazing options and features that cradle the balance between performance and power.

Time to have a ton of fun for quite an affordable price.  After all, we bet you'd expect to pay much more for a 1965 Ford Mustang with a wild paint job, custom interior, four-on-the-floor, and an upgraded V8 under that cool Cobra Jet hood.

We could tell you this is a red-hot deal, but you already know that from the paint.  The custom flames make a bold first impression as they consume the front end and make their way down this first-year Mustang's iconic profile.  But don't let that be your only deciding factor on this coupe.  Take a look at the rest of the quality work.  For example, the gray paint that covers the rest of the car has a great metallic element and plenty of shine to make sure that the whole body looks great.  And you have great iconic details like the fog lights from the GT package, and GT wheels from the later pony cars.  And speaking of those muscle Mustangs, don't you just love how this one utilizes the Cobra Jet shaker hood?

Inside, the custom performance feeling continues with a leather bucket seat interior borrowed from a later-model Mustang.  That means you get upgraded comfort, while still getting the iconic pony embroidered on the seatback.  Plus, the cup holder center console is a great place to rest your elbow when your right hand is on the Hurst stick shift.  And your left hand is going to love the grippy Gant GT sports steering wheel.   While this has an upgraded AM/FM/CD stereo, all these performance pieces are a clear sign your favorite soundtrack will really be the rumble of the dual exhaust.

While the interior and exterior have a bold standout presence, the engine bay is all about getting down to business.  Within the black walls you can see the 289 cubic-inch motor's bold blue block radiating power.  Plus, with the fresh air topper feeding the Edelbrock four-barrel carburetor, you know there's extra power coming from the V8.  You have complete control over this motor thanks to the four-speed top loader stick shift.  As you look over all the photos, you're going to spot all the right supporting components, like front disc brakes and an adjustable coilover rear suspension.  There's even a Champion aluminum radiator w/electric fan to keep this whole package running cool.

So beneath the cool custom appearance lies the right pieces for a sturdy performance machine.  It's amazing all of this can be so affordable, but you're not the only one who thinks so.  That's why you need to hurry to grab this deal. Call now!

Up for sale in Gateway"??s 1 showroom is this very clean & classic 1969 Ford Mustang Grande.  1969 saw the addition of the third restyling of the Mustang with more heft to the body with it being extended almost 4 inches ad the width increased by a half an inch.  The Grande edition was also a new edition as a luxury model that featured a softer ride extra sound deadening material added to the car as well as a deluxe interior with wood trim.  This one is powered by a 351 CiD V8 Windsor motor that runs strong & healthy throughout the power band.   The car in an M code car and originally came with a 390 V8.  The extremely popular 351 is paired to a C4 3-speed automatic transmission that shifts smoothly up & down through the gears.  The engine bay is clean and rust free.   All wires and components are neatly mounted and placed & it does have Ford polished valve covers & air cleaner.  The car also has dual exhaust. The exterior of the car is in very nice condition.  The paint is very nice and is free from any dings dents or major scratches.  The car does not have a very glossy finish but it is that of a very nice driver & still shows well.  The body panel gaps are even and the body is straight & true.  The polished trim is nice as well and doesn"??t require any attention.  The bumpers grill emblems & glass are also in very nice shape and are ready to roll.  The vinyl top is also in fantastic condition and is free from tears or blemishes.  Keeping the authentic classic look of the car is the original Ford hub cap wheels that are wrapped in newer radial tires that have plenty of life in them.  The interior is in excellent condition and is great looking on the Grande edition.  The vinyl & cloth seats are in superb condition and are comfortable.  The carpet dash door panels & headliner follow suit and are all in very nice shape.   The deluxe interior trim on the car is much different & unique when almost every other mustang on the market with the same basic look.   So it separates itself from the market with that factor.   The car is rust free and it was well cared for over the years.   The trunk is very clean as well.  The car looks just as good underneath it as it does on top.  New suspension & bushings are evident.  Car is believed to have original miles but it is not documented.  Options on this car include; power brakes power steering AM/FM with cassette white wall tires & more. For sale in our Detroit Showroom is an absolutely gorgeous 1968 Ford Mustang.  Upon its official debut in 1965 the Ford Mustang was Fords most successful launch since the Model A.  This iconic machine essentially created the term Pony Car and has been influencing the sports-car market ever since its birth. The Mustangs release took the entire automotive industry by storm.  It was only anticipated that Ford would sell less than 100000 Mustangs upon its arrival into the automotive world.  Boy were they wrong!  Ford produced over 1 million Mustangs within the first 18 months of its production due to the enormous demand. This meticulously maintained Mustang is sporting a beautiful Tahoe Turquoise Metallic paint job that is sure to turn heads wherever you decide to steer this Pony around. The inside is a very clean vinyl interior that is equipped with the bucket seats and floor shifter which sets off this Mustang perfectly.  This particular Mustang has more than enough power to get your motors going.  It is equipped with the original 289CID V8 that provides a very satisfying rumble as soon as you start this pristine Pony.  This potent V8 is matted to a C-4 3 Speed automatic transmission that effortlessly glides thru the gears allowing this Mustang to reach cruising speeds with ease.  The Mustang rests comfortably on a set of spotless chrome Cragar wheels with a newer set of Goodyear Eagle GT radial tires.  This pretty Pony also comes with an AM/FM Radio CD Player Power Steering vinyl interior and Seat Belts for safety. In September of 1965 Shelby American General Manager Peyton Cramer struck up a deal with Hertz, Inc. to offer their 1966 GT350H Mustang as a rental car. It was an interesting idea. Due to the harsh driving conditions that these cars were subjected to by rental drivers, many were taken out of commission and did not survive. Years later, originals that did endure are extremely valuable and easily net $150,000 or more at auction. Our 1965 Mustang coupe is a tribute to this Ford/Hertz concept. When it was restored 10 years ago, the exterior was refinished in Raven Black with GT350H gold accent stripes. Mustang GT steel wheels with radial tires and a classic GT hood scoop provide nice finishing touches to the exterior. The black vinyl interior was restored back to original. Some new elements include: seat upholstery/foam, carpeting, headliner, door panels/armrests, windshield glass and weather-stripping. The Mustang three-spoke wheel/horn components are also new and a Sony stereo furnishes your sounds. A Ford 302ci small block that is upgraded with an aluminum intake, Holley carburation, MSD ignition and tube headers w/2-1/2'' pipes powers our Mustang. It is backed by a 3-speed automatic transmission. The factory differential has new ring and pinion gears and new bearings. Brakes are standard 4-wheel drum units with new shoes and cylinders. This is a very nice Mustang GT350H tribute car that will sell quickly. ALL VEHICLES SOLD ''AS IS''.
